 Bisi Kazeem of FRSC  The Corps Public Education Officer, Mr Bisi Kazeem, disclosed this in an SMS alert to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Abuja on Sunday. Kazeem said 24 vehicles, including 3 ambulances, would also be deployed for the exercise. The aim, according to him, is to strictly enforce the expected restriction in vehicular movement, and to ensure there are no crashes before and after the polls.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .